WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.300
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>Prologue.

00:00:01.300 --> 00:00:06.578
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>I did not set out to write a book, ever,
really. But this book grew within me,

00:00:06.578 --> 00:00:12.129
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>from a question I could not stop asking,
and that question sprung from a season of

00:00:12.129 --> 00:00:14.117
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>emptiness I had not expected.

00:00:14.117 --> 00:00:18.836
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>I was raised in a Christian home, but the
faith I inherited was more like

00:00:18.836 --> 00:00:24.014
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>furniture. It was just there. I did not
think about it much. By my late twenties

00:00:24.014 --> 00:00:29.061
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>I had drifted far enough from it that the
distance no longer registered in any

00:00:29.061 --> 00:00:33.780
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>practical way. What did register,
eventually, was an emptyness carved out

00:00:33.780 --> 00:00:38.368
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>by the popular atheism I had wandered
into. The arguments were loud and

00:00:38.368 --> 00:00:43.545
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>confident and dissapointingly incurious.
They attacked a God I did not recognise

00:00:43.545 --> 00:00:47.740
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>from any serious theology I had
encountered, and they claimed the

00:00:47.740 --> 00:00:52.263
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>authority of science while showing
remarkably little interest in where

00:00:52.263 --> 00:00:57.047
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>science was actually uncertain. The
rhetoric was polished, to be sure. But

00:00:57.047 --> 00:01:02.094
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>the substance was wafer thin. I remember
one evening, having just finished yet

00:01:02.094 --> 00:01:07.272
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>another bestselling debunking of faith,
and thinking: if the case against God is

00:01:07.272 --> 00:01:10.680
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>this easy, someone is not asking the
tough questions.

00:01:10.680 --> 00:01:16.067
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>So I started asking them myself. Not as a
believer defending a position, but as

00:01:16.067 --> 00:01:21.248
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>someone genuinely unsettled, willing to
follow the inquiry wherever it might

00:01:21.248 --> 00:01:21.593
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>lead.

00:01:21.593 --> 00:01:27.059
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>That inquiry has now lasted more than two
decades, and it has taken me through

00:01:27.059 --> 00:01:32.169
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>terrain I never expected to cross. I
studied broadly at first: cosmology,

00:01:32.169 --> 00:01:37.706
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>quantum mechanics, evolutionary biology,
the philosophy of mind. And I read the

00:01:37.706 --> 00:01:42.745
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>primary sources as well as the popular
summaries, and whilst the popular

00:01:42.745 --> 00:01:47.714
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>summaries kept telling me things were
settled, when the academic papers

00:01:47.714 --> 00:01:53.392
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>indicated otherwise. I discovered, to my
surprise, that the confident materialism

00:01:53.392 --> 00:01:58.716
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>I had absorbed from popular culture
rested on interpretive choices that were

00:01:58.716 --> 00:02:03.826
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>far less secure than their public
presentation suggested. The science and

00:02:03.826 --> 00:02:09.079
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>the data was indisputable, but the
framework built around it was one option

00:02:09.079 --> 00:02:12.770
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>among several, and by no means the most
coherent one.

00:02:12.770 --> 00:02:15.835
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>Two encounters changed the direction of
my thinking.

00:02:15.835 --> 00:02:20.536
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>The first was a book about quantised
spacetime that I picked up in my early

00:02:20.536 --> 00:02:25.173
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>forties. It was speculative, and some of
its claims did not survive closer

00:02:25.173 --> 00:02:30.128
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>scrutiny. But buried in its pages was an
image that I could not shake: the idea

00:02:30.128 --> 00:02:35.146
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>that space itself might be a medium, a
superfluid, and that what we call gravity

00:02:35.146 --> 00:02:39.783
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>might be the behaviour of density
gradients within that medium rather than

00:02:39.783 --> 00:02:44.929
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>a mysterious force reaching across empty
space. The picture was intuitive in a way

00:02:44.929 --> 00:02:50.138
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>that no physics had been for me before. I
could *see* it. A massive object does not

00:02:50.138 --> 00:02:55.156
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>pull things towards itself through some
invisible tether. It changes the density

00:02:55.156 --> 00:02:59.984
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>of the medium around it, and nearby
objects respond to the gradient the way a

00:02:59.984 --> 00:03:02.461
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>leaf responds to a current in a stream.

00:03:02.461 --> 00:03:07.837
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>I was so moved by that idea that I went
looking for the serious physics behind

00:03:07.837 --> 00:03:12.515
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>it. And I found it. Not in the
speculative book that had sparked the

00:03:12.515 --> 00:03:17.821
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>question, but in the peer-reviewed work
of physicists like Grigory Volovik at

00:03:17.821 --> 00:03:23.336
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>Aalto University, whose monograph *The
Universe in a Helium Droplet* showed that

00:03:23.336 --> 00:03:28.293
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>a superfluid medium can reproduce the
structures of particle physics and

00:03:28.293 --> 00:03:34.018
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>general relativity as emergent phenomena.
I found it in Kerson Huang's work at MIT,

00:03:34.018 --> 00:03:39.394
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>extending superfluid cosmology into a
coherent mathematical framework. I found

00:03:39.394 --> 00:03:44.561
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>it in Lasha Berezhiani and Justin
Khoury's superfluid dark matter programme

00:03:44.561 --> 00:03:49.727
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>at the University of Pennsylvania, which
explained galactic rotation curves

00:03:49.727 --> 00:03:55.103
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>without invisible particles. These were
not fringe thinkers. They were working

00:03:55.103 --> 00:03:59.711
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>physicists, publishing in refereed
journals, building on decades of

00:03:59.711 --> 00:04:04.040
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>condensed matter research that had
already earned Nobel Prizes.

00:04:04.040 --> 00:04:09.097
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>The framework they described is called
the superfluid vacuum hypothesis. It

00:04:09.097 --> 00:04:14.428
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>proposes, in essence, that the quantum
vacuum, the thing we loosely call "empty

00:04:14.428 --> 00:04:19.485
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>space," behaves as a superfluid at
cosmological scales. If this is correct,

00:04:19.485 --> 00:04:24.542
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>then the particles and forces we observe
are not fundamental ingredients of

00:04:24.542 --> 00:04:30.009
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>reality but emergent patterns within that
deeper medium, the way vortices are not

00:04:30.009 --> 00:04:32.879
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>separate from the water in which they
form.

00:04:32.879 --> 00:04:37.755
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>The second encounter was with an
equation. Euler's identity:

00:04:37.755 --> 00:04:43.049
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>e, to the power of i, times pie, plus
one, equals zero.

00:04:43.049 --> 00:04:47.565
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>I had always known it as a piece of
mathematical elegance, a curiosity to

00:04:47.565 --> 00:04:51.955
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>admire. But as I lived with the
superfluid picture and read more deeply

00:04:51.955 --> 00:04:56.973
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>into the theology I had once set aside,
the equation began to look like something

00:04:56.973 --> 00:05:01.113
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>else. Its five symbols, drawn from
completely unrelated branches of

00:05:01.113 --> 00:05:06.068
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>mathematics, combined into a statement
that was not merely true but structurally

00:05:06.068 --> 00:05:08.451
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>resonant with the oldest story I knew.

00:05:08.451 --> 00:05:14.914
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>Three of those symbols — e, i, and pie —
encode growth, a hidden perpendicular

00:05:14.914 --> 00:05:21.042
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>dimension, and the geometry of the
circle. Raised together as an exponent,

00:05:21.042 --> 00:05:27.337
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>they trace a half-turn through the
complex plane and land on negative one: a

00:05:27.337 --> 00:05:33.548
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>complete inversion. The equation then
adds one, and the result is zero. Not

00:05:33.548 --> 00:05:35.479
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>emptiness — resolution.

00:05:35.479 --> 00:05:40.794
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>I am not a mathematician by training, and
I will not pretend this is a proof of

00:05:40.794 --> 00:05:46.040
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>anything. But I will say plainly what I
saw, and what this book will spend its

00:05:46.040 --> 00:05:51.287
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>middle chapters carefully examining: the
structure of that equation maps, with

00:05:51.287 --> 00:05:56.602
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>uncanny precision, onto the Christian
narrative of creation, fall, incarnation,

00:05:56.602 --> 00:06:01.440
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>and restoration. Not as a metaphor or a
loose analogy, but as structural

00:06:01.440 --> 00:06:06.005
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>correspondence, symbol by symbol,
operation by operation. The middle

00:06:06.005 --> 00:06:11.252
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>chapters of this book exist to lay that
correspondence out in full, and I will

00:06:11.252 --> 00:06:16.703
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>not rush through it here. But I knew, the
first time the picture came into focus,

00:06:16.703 --> 00:06:21.609
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>that I was looking at something
breathtaking that I simply could not walk

00:06:21.609 --> 00:06:22.290
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>away from.

00:06:22.290 --> 00:06:27.232
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>I need to say something about that word
"maps" before we go any further, because

00:06:27.232 --> 00:06:29.860
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>it carries the weight of the whole
project.

00:06:29.860 --> 00:06:34.957
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>This book does not claim that Euler's
identity proves God exists. It does not

00:06:34.957 --> 00:06:40.322
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>claim that physics demonstrates the truth
of Christianity. It does not claim that

00:06:40.322 --> 00:06:45.351
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>the superfluid vacuum hypothesis is
established science. The hypothesis is a

00:06:45.351 --> 00:06:50.448
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>serious research programme, pursued by
credible physicists and supported by a

00:06:50.448 --> 00:06:55.142
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>growing body of experimental and
observational evidence, but it has not

00:06:55.142 --> 00:06:59.971
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>yet achieved consensus. It may prove
correct in time or it may even prove

00:06:59.971 --> 00:07:04.397
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>partly correct. It might also be
superseded by something altogether

00:07:04.397 --> 00:07:05.805
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>different and better.

00:07:05.805 --> 00:07:10.059
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>No. The claim of this book is
conditional, and I lean into that

00:07:10.059 --> 00:07:14.861
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>conditionality as the intellectual
backbone of everything that follows:

00:07:14.861 --> 00:07:19.765
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>**IF** the superfluid vacuum hypothesis
proves correct, **THEN** a striking set

00:07:19.765 --> 00:07:24.354
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>of structural resonances emerge between
the physics of that medium and the

00:07:24.354 --> 00:07:29.383
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>theological account of reality that the
Christian tradition has confessed for two

00:07:29.383 --> 00:07:30.326
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>thousand years.

00:07:30.326 --> 00:07:35.258
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>These resonances are not vague gestures
toward "isn't the universe amazing." They

00:07:35.258 --> 00:07:39.944
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>are specific, detailed, and testable
assertions in the sense that the physics

00:07:39.944 --> 00:07:44.383
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>underneath them will be confirmed or
disproven by future research. If the

00:07:44.383 --> 00:07:48.823
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>physics fails, the resonances fall with
it. The theology though, grounded

00:07:48.823 --> 00:07:53.323
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>independently in Scripture and the
historic confessions of the church will

00:07:53.323 --> 00:07:58.071
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>remain. Nothing in this book asks the
reader to stake their faith on a physics

00:07:58.071 --> 00:08:03.003
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>hypothesis. But everything in this book
asks the reader to consider what it would

00:08:03.003 --> 00:08:07.689
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>mean if the deepest structure of the
physical world turned out to confess the

00:08:07.689 --> 00:08:10.032
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>deepest claims of the Christian faith.

00:08:10.032 --> 00:08:15.224
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>That is the question I could not eject.
It is the question that turned a drifting

00:08:15.224 --> 00:08:20.222
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>ex-churchgoer into a person who reads
condensed matter physics papers, studies

00:08:20.222 --> 00:08:25.349
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>Reformed theology alone and in groups,
and who spends time marking Bible studies

00:08:25.349 --> 00:08:30.087
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>of men in prison and writing letters to
encourage them in their search for

00:08:30.087 --> 00:08:31.580
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>meaning and absolution.

00:08:31.580 --> 00:08:35.417
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>I should tell you what kind of book this
is, so you can decide whether to keep

00:08:35.417 --> 00:08:38.407
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>walking with me. But first, let me make
clear what it is not.

00:08:38.407 --> 00:08:43.494
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>This is not a book that attacks science.
I love science. I have spent the better

00:08:43.494 --> 00:08:48.774
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>part of twenty years studying it with the
careful, sometimes obsessive attention of

00:08:48.774 --> 00:08:53.153
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>someone who suspects it has something
extraordinary to say. This book

00:08:53.153 --> 00:08:58.047
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>celebrates what science has revealed
while asking honest questions about what

00:08:58.047 --> 00:09:02.877
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>it has not yet explained and about
whether the framework we use to interpret

00:09:02.877 --> 00:09:05.388
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>the evidence is the only one available.

00:09:05.388 --> 00:09:10.320
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>This is not a book about intelligent
design, at least not in the way that it

00:09:10.320 --> 00:09:15.055
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>has been used in recent political and
educational controversies. I am not

00:09:15.055 --> 00:09:19.329
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>arguing that certain biological
structures are too complex to have

00:09:19.329 --> 00:09:24.393
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>evolved, or that gaps in our knowledge
are evidence for God. The argument here

00:09:24.393 --> 00:09:29.062
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>is structural, not interventionist. It
concerns the deep architecture of

00:09:29.062 --> 00:09:32.416
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>physical law, not the details of
biological history.

00:09:32.416 --> 00:09:37.539
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>This is not a book of natural theology in
the classical sense either. I am not

00:09:37.539 --> 00:09:42.263
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>claiming to prove God's existence from
the evidence of nature alone. The

00:09:42.263 --> 00:09:47.319
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>Christian tradition has always held that
creation points beyond itself, and I

00:09:47.319 --> 00:09:52.309
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>believe it does, but a pointer is not a
proof. The resonances I describe are

00:09:52.309 --> 00:09:56.634
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>suggestive, detailed, and worth taking
seriously. But they are not

00:09:56.634 --> 00:09:57.632
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>demonstrations.

00:09:57.632 --> 00:10:02.463
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>And this is most certainly not a New Age
book. You will find no talk of

00:10:02.463 --> 00:10:07.570
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>"vibrations" or "energy fields" or
"quantum consciousness" in the way those

00:10:07.570 --> 00:10:12.677
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>phrases circulate in alternative wellness
culture. When this book discusses

00:10:12.677 --> 00:10:16.955
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>vibrations, it names the governing
equations. When it discusses

00:10:16.955 --> 00:10:22.269
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>consciousness, it draws hard boundaries
around what the physics can and cannot

00:10:22.269 --> 00:10:27.652
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>say. Every physical claim in these pages
is tethered to peer-reviewed research,

00:10:27.652 --> 00:10:32.138
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>and where the tether is long or
uncertain, it will be pointed out.

00:10:32.138 --> 00:10:36.773
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>What this book *is*, I hope, is a
fireside conversation starter. I have

00:10:36.773 --> 00:10:41.872
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>spent a long time in two worlds that most
people are told cannot speak to each

00:10:41.872 --> 00:10:47.302
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>other: the world of physics and the world
of faith. I have found that they speak to

00:10:47.302 --> 00:10:52.334
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>each other more fluently than either
side’s gatekeepers tend to admit. I want

00:10:52.334 --> 00:10:57.632
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>to show you what I have seen, as plainly
and honestly as I can, and let you judge

00:10:57.632 --> 00:11:00.744
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>for yourself whether the picture holds
together.

00:11:00.744 --> 00:11:05.597
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>You do not need a physics degree to read
this book, I certainly don’t posess one.

00:11:05.597 --> 00:11:09.783
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>And like me, you also do not need a
theology degree. You need only the

00:11:09.783 --> 00:11:14.455
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>willingness to think carefully and the
patience to let unfamiliar ideas arrive

00:11:14.455 --> 00:11:19.004
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>at their own pace. I will attempt to
explain every technical concept with no

00:11:19.004 --> 00:11:23.736
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>assumption of prior knowledge, in plain
language and with the same care I would

00:11:23.736 --> 00:11:28.529
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>use if we were sitting across a table and
you had asked me to tell you about the

00:11:28.529 --> 00:11:31.441
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>strangest, most beautiful thing I had
ever found.

00:11:31.441 --> 00:11:34.367
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>The journey ahead moves through five
parts.

00:11:34.367 --> 00:11:39.444
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>The first, *Learning to Read the World*,
builds the tools you need to evaluate

00:11:39.444 --> 00:11:44.850
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>scientific claims honestly. We begin with
the sky: how we measure cosmic distances,

00:11:44.850 --> 00:11:49.861
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>what the evidence for the expansion of
the universe actually shows, where the

00:11:49.861 --> 00:11:54.476
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>standard model's placeholders (dark
matter, dark energy, inflation) are

00:11:54.476 --> 00:11:59.091
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>genuinely explanatory and where they are
terms for things we do not yet

00:11:59.091 --> 00:12:03.970
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>understand. Then we come down to the
small: what quantum mechanics actually

00:12:03.970 --> 00:12:09.178
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>claims, what a field is, what the vacuum
looks like when you examine it closely,

00:12:09.178 --> 00:12:14.518
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>and why the language of waves, phase, and
rotation turns out to be the language in

00:12:14.518 --> 00:12:19.002
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>which the physical world prefers to
speak. By the time we finish that

00:12:19.002 --> 00:12:24.342
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>section, you will have what I think of as
a conscience about evidence, the ability

00:12:24.342 --> 00:12:29.484
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>to tell when a claim is standing on solid
ground, when it is standing on a good

00:12:29.484 --> 00:12:32.649
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>guess, and when it is standing on nothing
at all.

00:12:32.649 --> 00:12:37.671
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>The second part, *A Deeper Architecture*,
introduces the superfluid vacuum

00:12:37.671 --> 00:12:43.312
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>hypothesis properly. What does it mean to
say space is a medium? What is emergence,

00:12:43.312 --> 00:12:48.747
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>and why does it matter? How does gravity
arise from density gradients instead of

00:12:48.747 --> 00:12:53.976
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>mysterious forces? And why might this
particular medium, if it exists, be the

00:12:53.976 --> 00:12:59.066
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>kind of thing a Creator would make? That
last question is where the physics

00:12:59.066 --> 00:13:02.231
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>register gives way to the theological
register.

00:13:02.231 --> 00:13:07.039
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>The third part, *The Equation*, is the
mathematical heart of the book. This is

00:13:07.039 --> 00:13:11.910
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>where the argument is most original and
most vulnerable, and I hope to treat it

00:13:11.910 --> 00:13:13.284
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>with appropriate care.

00:13:13.284 --> 00:13:17.536
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>The fourth part, *Resonances and
Boundaries*, follows the implications

00:13:17.536 --> 00:13:22.404
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>further than you might expect and then
draws hard lines around what the argument

00:13:22.404 --> 00:13:27.148
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>can and cannot reach, because a book that
does not name its own limits has not

00:13:27.148 --> 00:13:29.120
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>earned the right to make claims.

00:13:29.120 --> 00:13:33.823
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>The fifth part, *The Invitation*, draws
the threads together. Not to agree with

00:13:33.823 --> 00:13:38.466
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>me, necessarily. But to consider the
possibility that the cosmos is not a cold

00:13:38.466 --> 00:13:43.049
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>accident, that its structure might be
saying something, and that what it says

00:13:43.049 --> 00:13:47.270
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>might rhyme with the oldest confession
the church has made: that in the

00:13:47.270 --> 00:13:51.551
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>beginning was the Word, and the Word was
with God, and the Word was God.

00:13:51.551 --> 00:13:56.099
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>I write as a Reformed Christian. That
means I stand within a particular

00:13:56.099 --> 00:14:01.037
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>tradition: the heritage of John Calvin,
the Belgic Confession, the Heidelberg

00:14:01.037 --> 00:14:05.975
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>Catechism. I will try be honest about
where that tradition shapes my reading,

00:14:05.975 --> 00:14:10.978
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>and I will use the broadest accurate
language I can, because most of what this

00:14:10.978 --> 00:14:15.981
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>book describes belongs not to Reformed
theology specifically but to the shared

00:14:15.981 --> 00:14:18.905
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>confession of Christians across two
millennia.

00:14:18.905 --> 00:14:23.763
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>As I mentioned above, I write also as
someone who mentors men in prison. When a

00:14:23.763 --> 00:14:28.496
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>man who has lost everything writes to ask
whether the universe has a purpose,

00:14:28.496 --> 00:14:33.292
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>whether his life counts for something,
whether there is a God who sees him and

00:14:33.292 --> 00:14:38.150
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>might forgive him, the question deserves
an answer that is honest about what we

00:14:38.150 --> 00:14:42.883
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>know and what we do not. I have tried to
write a book that could be read in a

00:14:42.883 --> 00:14:47.180
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>study group in that setting, with no
resources beyond the text and the

00:14:47.180 --> 00:14:48.488
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>willingness to think.

00:14:48.488 --> 00:14:52.960
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>If the language is too technical, I will
have failed. If the theology is too

00:14:52.960 --> 00:14:57.372
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>academic, I will have failed. If the
wonder is not felt, I will have failed

00:14:57.372 --> 00:14:58.147
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>worst of all.

00:14:58.147 --> 00:15:03.068
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>This is a book about evidence, mystery,
and the place where they meet. It asks of

00:15:03.068 --> 00:15:07.866
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>you the courage to ask *what if*, the
discipline to follow the answer carefully

00:15:07.866 --> 00:15:11.926
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>and honestly, and the openness to
consider a unity of two worlds of

00:15:11.926 --> 00:15:16.477
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>knowledge that might fill you with the
same reverence for the wonder of our

00:15:16.477 --> 00:15:16.908
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>cosmos.

00:15:16.908 --> 00:15:18.208
<v Christopher - Smooth, calm and very English>Let us begin.

